# Code Quality Rules

This project follows comprehensive coding standards and patterns documented in `.cursor/code-quality-rules.md`.

For detailed rules and patterns, see: `.cursor/code-quality-rules.md`

## Quick Reference

- **Project Structure**: Next.js App Router with organized directories (`src/app/`, `src/lib/`, `src/ui/`, etc.)
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode, explicit return types, use `@/*` path aliases
- **Components**: Default to Server Components, use `"use client"` only when needed
- **Error Handling**: Use `logError` utility, return `null` on errors, handle gracefully
- **Database**: Prisma singleton pattern with Accelerate extension
- **Server Actions**: Use `"use server"`, return `{ success: boolean; message: string }`
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with `cn()` utility, support dark mode
- **File Naming**: kebab-case for actions/utils, PascalCase for components, camelCase for hooks

See `.cursor/code-quality-rules.md` for complete documentation.
